<html><head><title>VN Global News: Aion Database Launches </title></head><body class="newsbody" ><div class=newbody><h2>EverQuest Vault -- EQ </h3><h3>VN Global News: Aion Database Launches </h3><p>Looking to find the hard details for one of the campaign quests in Aion? Or maybe you are seeking the lowdown on your level 50 Archon Tribunus's Sword? Look no further than IGN's <a href="http://aion.ign.com/">Aion Tower</a> website for all your game database needs. The site has just launched a super extensive <a href="http://db.aion.ign.com/">game database</a> for the MMO title, Aion. <br> <br> Saying it's extensive might be an understatement. The site goes beyond listing everything you can find in the game. These include: items, recipes, quests, zones, NPCs, skills, maps, and everything else. It goes beyond that by providing 3D viewers, Grind Planer, Stigma Planner, Item comparisons, browser plugins, and so much more. This database is impressive. <br> <br>Drop by today - <a href="http://db.aion.ign.com/">Aion Database</a></div><p><div classs=copyright><font face=arial size=2 color=#959595>News Story from EverQuest Vault -- EQ <br>News Date: Monday, 14 Dec, 2009<br>Link: <a href="http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=55481">http://eqvault.ign.com/fullstory.php?id=55481</a><br>Printed On: Thu Apr 12 16:41:50 PDT 2012<br>©2008 IGN Entertainment</font></span>